## Water Parameters

**Temperature:** 23–28°C. Target 26°C for optimal health and activity. Breeding pairs benefit from 27–28°C.

**pH:** 6.0–8.0. Oscars are genuinely tolerant of a wide pH range — one of the few cichlids that thrives in neutral tap water without adjustment.

**Hardness:** 5–20 dGH. Flexible. Moderately hard water is absolutely fine.

**Ammonia / Nitrite:** Zero. Despite their hardy reputation, consistent ammonia exposure causes HITH (hole-in-the-head disease) and shortens lifespan.

**Nitrate:** Below 20 ppm. With their waste production this requires significant weekly water changes — 30–50% per week minimum.

