## Filtration

Oscar tanks require *substantial* over-filtration. They are messy eaters and heavy waste producers — the standard advice of 10x turnover rate per hour applies here, with 15x being better.

**Canister filters** are the standard choice — high capacity media, powerful flow, easy to clean externally without disturbing the tank. Run two canisters on a large Oscar tank, either in parallel or in series (one for mechanical, one biological filtration).

**Sump systems** — Used by serious Oscar keepers. Massive biological filtration capacity, easy maintenance, good for large setups.

**Avoid:** Hang-on-back filters as primary filtration on adult Oscar tanks — insufficient capacity.

