## Feeding

### Diet

Oscars are carnivores. Their natural diet consists of fish, crustaceans, and large invertebrates.

**Pellets** — High-quality cichlid pellets (protein content 40%+) form the practical staple. Large pellet sizes for adult fish. Brands like Hikari Cichlid Gold, NLS Cichlid Formula, and Massivore pellets are well-regarded.

**Frozen foods:**
- Frozen krill — Excellent protein and colour-enhancing carotenoids
- Frozen bloodworm — Accepted; lower in nutrition than krill but useful for variety
- Frozen silversides / lance fish — Whole fish; mirrors natural diet composition
- Frozen prawns (shell-on) — Good dental stimulation and nutrition

**Live foods (supplemental):**
- **Earthworms** — Highly relished; nutritionally balanced and readily accepted. Can be collected or purchased from fishing suppliers.
- **Crickets / locusts** (gut-loaded) — Surface insects that trigger intense predation response
- **Baby Brine Shrimp** — Useful for conditioning and juveniles. **[Available at Blackwater Aquatics](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/collections/live-foods).**

### Foods to Avoid

**Feeder goldfish / feeder guppies** — Despite being commonly suggested, feeder fish carry disease and parasites, create nutritional imbalances (excess thiaminase in goldfish), and encourage aggressive behavioural conditioning. Avoid entirely.

**Mammal flesh** (beef heart, chicken) — High in saturated fats that fish metabolisms cannot process efficiently; causes fatty liver disease over time.

**Mealworms in excess** — High chitin content; digestive issues if used as a staple.

