## Tankmates

Oscars are predators. Anything smaller than approximately 10–12 cm is at serious risk of being eaten. Tankmates must be:
- Large enough not to fit in the Oscar's mouth
- Hardy enough to withstand periodic aggression
- Comfortable at similar temperatures

**Compatible options:**
- Plecostomus species (large — Common Pleco, Sailfin Pleco) — Armoured; Oscar ignores them
- Large Cichlids (Jack Dempsey, Firemouth, Green Terror) — Require careful monitoring; territory disputes are common
- Large catfish (Synodontis, Pimelodidae) — Often work well
- Large Knife Fish (Black Ghost Knife) — Usually compatible in large tanks

**Never keep with:**
- Small fish of any species
- Shrimp or invertebrates
- Small plecos (will be eaten)
- Angelfish

