## Colour Varieties

**Wild-type:** Dark grey/black base with orange-red patches and the distinctive orange-ringed "ocellus" (eye spot) on the tail base — a false-eye predator deflection mechanism.

**Red Oscar:** Predominantly red and orange colouration; most common aquarium form.

**Tiger Oscar:** Dark base with red-orange striped pattern.

**Albino Oscar:** Cream/white body with pink eyes. Red or Tiger albino variants exist.

**Long-fin Oscar:** Extended fin rays; less common; more prone to fin damage.

