## Hole-in-the-Head Disease (HITH)

The most common Oscar-specific disease. Characterised by pitting and erosion around the lateral line and on the head. Causes:
- Chronic high nitrate (the most common trigger)
- Activated carbon use (disputed but many experienced keepers see correlation)
- Hexamita protozoan infection
- Poor diet / vitamin deficiency

**Treatment:** Improve water quality immediately (large daily water changes), remove activated carbon, treat with Metronidazole if active infection suspected, supplement with vitamins.

**Prevention:** Maintain nitrate below 20 ppm through consistent water changes. Feed a varied, vitamin-rich diet. Activated carbon should be used sparingly if at all.

